--- title: "Oregon FQHC Landscape" subtitle: "Automated analysis of Health Center Service Delivery Sites" author: "E. Pitzer" date: last-modified categories: [Data Engineering, Healthcare, Python] format: html: code-fold: true toc: true page-layout: full jupyter: python3 --- ## Project Status **Phase 2: Geospatial & Search** | [View Technical Architecture →](about.qmd) Data is sourced directly from the [HRSA Data Warehouse](https://data.hrsa.gov/). ### At a Glance We are currently tracking **329** service delivery sites across **83** cities in Oregon. ### Sites by County (Top 10) Where are the health center sites concentrated? ::: {#cell-fig-county-dist .cell execution_count=2} ``` {.python .cell-code} # Configure the visual style sns.set_theme(style="whitegrid") plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6)) # Count sites per county - USING CORRECTED COLUMN NAME county_counts = df['county'].value_counts().head(10).reset_index() county_counts.columns = ['County', 'Sites'] # Plot ax = sns.barplot(data=county_counts, x='Sites', y='County', palette="viridis", hue='County') ax.set_title("Top 10 Counties by Number of Sites") plt.show() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![Distribution of FQHC Sites by County](index_files/figure-html/fig-county-dist-output-1.png){#fig-county-dist width=873 height=529} ::: ::: ### Interactive Map Hover over points to see site details. ::: {#cell-fig-map .cell execution_count=3} ``` {.python .cell-code} # Define a custom color sequence if you want specific branding, # otherwise Plotly handles it automatically. fig = px.scatter_mapbox( df, lat="latitude", lon="longitude", hover_name="site_name", hover_data=["organization", "city", "county"], color="organization", zoom=5.5, center={"lat": 44.0, "lon": -120.5}, height=600, title="Oregon FQHC Sites by Organization" ) fig.update_layout( mapbox_style="open-street-map", margin={"r":0,"t":40,"l":0,"b":0}, legend=dict( orientation="h", # Horizontal yanchor="top", # Anchor the top of the legend... y=-0.05, # ...just below the map xanchor="center", # Center it x=0.5, title=None, # REMOVE the title (fixes the "zation" cutoff) font=dict(size=9), # Smaller font to fit more items itemsizing='constant' ) ) fig.show() ``` ::: {#fig-map .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` Map of Health Center Service Delivery Sites ::: ::: ### Search & Explore Data Use the search bar below to find specific clinics, cities, or organizations. ::: {#tbl-interactive .cell execution_count=4} ``` {.python .cell-code} # Display interactive table with search show(df[['organization', 'site_name', 'city', 'county', 'type']], classes="display nowrap compact", paging=True, searching=True) # <--- Enables the Search Bar ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
